# Nespresso mobile row cascade (no stuck chains)

Mobile Nespresso timeline rows in `mobile-case-nav.css` use independent `translateY` per row. **`~ .timeline-item` stack rules override exact per-row chains** when the stack selector is longer / later and the row only has a class hook.

## What broke (repeat offender)

```css
/* BAD — ~ hits rows 10–12; beats class-only row 12 */
.header + .item × 8 + .item ~ .item { transform: translateY(3473px); }

/* LOSES — class-only specificity too low */
.timeline-item--nespresso-mobile-only { transform: translateY(12011px); }
```

Mega menu row 12 was stuck at **3473px** while edits to **12011px** appeared to do nothing.

## Do

- **One exact N-chain per independently tuned row** — count `.timeline-item` siblings after `.timeline-header` (row 12 = 12× `+ .timeline-item`).
- End the chain on the row’s class when it has one, e.g. `+ .timeline-item.timeline-item--nespresso-mobile-only`.
- If a baseline stack rule is needed, use **exact chain only** — no `~ .timeline-item` on rows that have (or will have) per-row chains below.
- On any remaining `~` baselines, exclude mobile-only rows:  
  `~ .timeline-item:not(.timeline-item--nespresso-mobile-only)`.

## Do not

- Add `~ .timeline-item { transform: … }` below row 8+ when rows 9–12 already have exact chains.
- Move a row with **class-only** selectors when rows above use long `~` stacks.
- Split image/text with flex `order` — move the whole `.timeline-item` (see `timeline-image-text-linked`).
- **Revert or “restore” sections 1–10** when fixing row 12 cascade — append a 12-chain rule only; leave approved squiggle/row values untouched.

## Required check after row/squiggle tuning

1. Edit row `translateY` → hard refresh → row actually moves.
2. If a row ignores CSS, grep `mobile-case-nav.css` for `~ .timeline-item` and compare selector specificity vs the row’s N-chain.
